cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.DB 

This paper deals with security and privacy issues related to passwords and their reuse on the web. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of private set-membership-test protocol, which falls under the category of cs.CY (Computers and Society). The paper also involves optimization of parameters based on insights of how passwords tend to be reused, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper involves the use of techniques to mitigate leakage, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases).
